    "contenu": "Here are the structured contents of the document containing recipes for three different punches:\n\n### Aperol Punch\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 2 ounces Aperol\n- 2 ounces grapefruit juice\n- 2 ounces lemon juice\n- 4 dashes House Peychaud's bitters\n- Garnish: 6 grapefruit crescents\n- 8 ounces of club soda (divided into 4 ounces in mix and 4 ounces to top off)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a pitcher, muddle the sugar cubes with 4 ounces of the club soda until the sugar is fully broken up.\n2. Add the Aperol, grapefruit juice, lemon juice, and bitters.\n3. Fill the pitcher three-quarters full with ice cubes.\n4. Stir until cold, then strain into a punch bowl over 1 large block of ice.\n5. Top with the remaining 4 ounces of club soda.\n6. Garnish with the grapefruit crescents and serve with a ladle and punch glasses.\n\n---\n\n### Bloodhound Punch\n\n**Author:** Jason Littrell, 2009\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 8 ounces Elijah Craig 12-Year Bourbon\n- 4 ounces Donn's Spices #2\n- 3 ounces lemon juice\n- 4 ounces blueberry syrup\n- Garnish: 6 lemon wheels\n- 6 ounces club soda \n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a pitcher, combine all the ingredients except the club soda.\n2. Fill the pitcher three-quarters full with ice cubes.\n3. Stir until cold, then strain into a punch bowl over 1 large block of ice.\n4. Top with the club soda.\n5. Garnish with lemon wheels and serve with a ladle and punch glasses.\n\n---\n\n### Bookhouse Boys Punch\n\n**Author:** Jessica Gonzalez, 2011\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 3 ounces chamomile-infused Old Overholt Rye\n- 3 ounces Old Weller Antique 107 Bourbon\n- 3 ounces Donn's Mix #1\n- 1½ ounces grapefruit juice\n- 1½ ounces lemon juice\n- ¼ ounce acacia honey syrup\n- ¼ ounce ginger syrup\n- 5 ounces club soda                 \n- Garnish: 5 lemon wheels              \n\n**Instructions:**\n1. No specific instructions provided.\n\nThese recipes offer a variety of punch options, featuring different types of liquors and unique mixes, suitable for various occasions and tastes. Each recipe provides specific measurements for a balanced flavor and includes garnishing tips to enhance the visual presentation and taste."
