    "source": "Death_&_Co__Modern_Classic_Cocktails,_with_More_than_500_Recipes_(_PDFDrive_).pdf_page_509",
    "contenu": "The document contains recipes for various food preparations. Below is the structured content, presented in a markdown format for each recipe:\n\n### KUMQUAT CORDIAL\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup granulated sugar\n- ½ cup thinly sliced kumquats\n- ¼ cup water\n- 2 tablespoons lime juice\n- 1½ tablespoons lemon juice\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a blender or food processor, combine all ingredients.\n2. Pulse until the kumquats are finely chopped.\n3. Transfer to a container, cover, and refrigerate for 24 hours.\n4. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve.\n5. Store in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.\n\n### PUMPKIN PUREE\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 15 oz can pure pumpkin puree\n- 15 oz Simple Syrup\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- ½ teaspoon ground ginger\n- ¼ teaspoon ground cloves\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. In a bowl, combine all the ingredients.\n2. Blend or whisk vigorously until combined.\n3. Store in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.\n\n### RED BELL PEPPER PUREE\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 coarsely chopped red bell pepper\n- Splash of water\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Combine ingredients in a blender.\n2. Blend until smooth.\n3. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve.\n4. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.\n\n### STRAWBERRY-BALSAMIC GASTRIQUE\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1⅓ cups superfine sugar\n- 1⅓ cups water\n- 2 cups hulled and halved strawberries\n- 1 cup balsamic vinegar\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Combine sugar and water in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves and mixture is heated but not boiling.\n2. Add strawberries and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.\n3. Add balsamic vinegar, increase heat, and bring to a boil.\n4. Lower heat and simmer until thickened, about 30 minutes.\n5. Strain through a cheesecloth-lined fine-mesh sieve.\n6. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.\n\n### TARRAGON AND AGAVE NECTAR GASTRIQUE\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 12 oz agave nectar\n- 4 oz champagne vinegar\n- ¼ cup gently muddled tarragon leaves\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Bring agave nectar to a boil in a saucepan over medium heat.\n2. Add champagne vinegar, stirring constantly.\n3. Boil for 5 minutes while stirring.\n4. Remove from heat, add tarragon leaves, and let cool.\n5. Strain through a cheesecloth-lined fine-mesh sieve, pressing to extract flavor.\n6. Store in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks."
